contentrichtext.text: '''James Moriarty''' may refer to: * [[James Moriarty (bishop)]] (born 1936), the Bishop Emeritus of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Kildare and Leighlin * [[James F. Moriarty]], United States diplomat and career foreign service officer * [[James Robert Moriarty]] (born 1946), American lawyer noted for mass torts against major corporations * [[Count Jim Moriarty]], fictional character from the 1950s BBC Radio comedy ''The Goon Show'' * [[Professor Moriarty]], fictional character and the archenemy of the detective Sherlock Holmes * [[Jim Moriarty]], New Zealand actor ==See also== *[[Jim Moriarty (disambiguation)]] {{hndis|Moriarty, James}}
